-- LSE Said to Hire Schwieger From Merrill as Equities Head
-- B y   S o f i a   H o r t a   e   C o s t a   a n d   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 2013-05-10T10:11:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-10/lse-said-to-hire-schwieger-from-merrill-as-equities-head.html
London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  hired
Brian Schwieger from Bank of America Corp.’s Merrill Lynch unit,
three people with knowledge of the plans said.  Schwieger will be based in London as head of equities at
the exchange operator, said one of the people, who asked not to
be identified because the details aren’t public.  He has been with Charlotte, North Carolina-based Bank of
America since August 2005 and is responsible for sales, marketing
and execution consulting for European equity electronic trading
in London, according to his LinkedIn  profile . He has also worked
for New York-based Morgan Stanley.  Spokeswomen for LSE and Merrill Lynch declined to comment
on the appointment.  To contact the reporters on this story:
